<p>and logarithms:</p>
<code>
differentiate (ln x)
   = x^-1
</code>
<p>as well as the integral of polynomials:</p>
<code>
integrate (x^3 - 4.5x^2 + 6x - 2)
   = (1/4)x^4 - (3/2)x^3 + 3x^2 - 2x + c
</code>
<p>the exact definite integral between 2 limits:</p>
<code>
integrate (x^3 - 4.5x^2 + 6x - 2, 2, 3)
   = 3/4
</code>
<p>and the same result via a variety of numerical methods:</p>
<code>
trapeziumrule (x^3 - 4.5x^2 + 6x - 2, 2, 3)
   = 0.75004999999999999449329379785922355949878692626953125
simpsonrule (x^3 - 4.5x^2 + 6x - 2, 2, 3)
   = 0.75000000000000011102230246251565404236316680908203125
romberg (x^3 - 4.5x^2 + 6x - 2, 2, 3)
   = 0.75
</code>
